From item extractions (Xelrin):<br>
<br>
Sentient Medallion with 5 charges of Resist Disease<br>
Gleaming Bauble, with 5 charges of Spikecoat<br>
Flawed Spell Creation, with 5 charges of Resist Magic<br>
<br>
One thing I find curious,(and I'm hoping I have a complete rendition of Balic's text) is that Balic doesn't appear to tell you to return anything to him. Word/rune extractions initially yield:<br>
<br>
Word of Combine <br>
Word of Sorcery<br>
Word of Impetus <br>
Word of the Helix <br>
<br>
Might these have to be returned to the specified assistants rather than Balic?<br>
With those assistants then providing a further clue? If this is true then Balic's rewards are indeed &quot;booby prizes&quot;.<br>
<br>
What makes this quest particularly trying is the fact that you are never quite certain that Verant has it working. For the life of me I cannot understand how you can design a quest and then program the quest and NOT (apparently) walk through<br>
the quest in game to make sure the damn thing works as intended. This was also evidenced in the Magic Manual quest as well where they had the various NPC's text criss-crossed.<br>
Any walk through of that quest prior to release should have revealed that. To me, this is really inexcusable to have not, at some point, verified in game that the quest is doable. So the question remains, is it doable now or are parts still broken?<br>
<br>
One other thing to consider is that only Gurynth gives you a clue as to how many extractions will be required. The other sages really do not define a number. Particularly in Xelrin's case, the number of extractions is open ended.<br>
<br>
